Q: What is the difference
between supervised and
unsupervised learning?
A: Supervised: model trained with labelled data (e.g., Linear Regression,
Naïve Bayes, SVM). Unsupervised: no labels, finds patterns (e.g., K-Means,
Hierarchical Clustering).

